JJ,<br><br>
You imply that I am just a naiive kid who is oversimplifying things by pointing my finger at the so-called 'big-bad evil military-industrial complex'.  I'm afraid you are guilty of a textbook logical fallacy by using my age to weaken my position.<br>
  <br>
What is so hard to understand about the fact that selling weapons to non-democratic governments with documented histories of human rights abuses is indeed, quite simply, evil?  An 8 year old could understand that as well as a 90 year old.  And any thoughtful American who has taken care to study our modern government understands very well that lobbyists and PACs (i.e. money) rule on Capitol Hill.  And there is no larger, stronger, or more well-funded lobby on Capitol Hill than the weapons/defense industry lobby (the weapons industry imploys a stunning 200+ lobbyists for every U.S. congressperson!  That's right, there are are over 20,000 well-paid, registered lobbyists on Capitol Hill employed by the weapons industry).  Yes indeed, my friend, the military-industrial complex is indeed very, very real, and very, very evil.  That is no oversimplification, any more than it is an oversimplification to say that innocent women and children were slaughtered by the hundreds of thousands in the Vietnam War, or by the tens of thousands in the Gulf War.<br><br>
Please don't dismiss these very real, critical issues as the naivetee of another idealistic kid.  These issues are every bit as real and evil as war and genocide themselves, which yes indeed are often direct byproducts of the good ol' American military-industrial complex.<br><br>
You're never too old to believe in simple ideals such as world peace and disarmament.  I'm sorry that you have apparently become too jaded and cynical to believe in these very simple, valid and yes, attainable ideals, and too sophisticated to see the weapons industry at face value.<br><br>
I am 31 years old.  I have already lost most of my idealism.   I understand that this world can and always will be at times a very ugly place.  I understand I may never see world peace and disarmament in my lifetime.  Is that any reason to stop believing in it and fighting for it?<br><br>
The emporer wears no clothes, old man. ;-)<br>

